25|$|Age: {{some people}} {{experience}} hangovers as getting worse as one ages. This {{is thought to}} be caused by declining supplies of alcohol dehydrogenase, the enzyme involved in metabolizing alcohol. Although it is actually unknown whether hangover symptoms and severity change with age, research shows <b>that</b> <b>drinking</b> patterns change across ages, and heavy drinking episodes that may result in hangover are much less often experienced as age increases.|$|E
